Victor Mela, a member of the House of Representatives, has been sentenced to prison.  The lawmaker was sentenced to one month imprisonment by a Magistrate Court in Wuse, Zone 6. The lawmaker who represents Billiri/Balanga federal constituency was, however, given an option of fine. PREMIUM TIMES had reported that a magistrate court had found the lawmaker guilty of lying under oath while filling the CD001 INEC form prior to the 2019 elections. He swore to an affidavit thrice, denying citizenship of another country while he has a British passport. His conviction follows prosecution by the police in Abuja. More details later….   By Hauwa Gold   Sokoto   -      A Sokoto Chief Magistrates’ Court on Friday sentenced a 32-year-old man, Sani Abdullahi, to 12 months in prison for attempting to steal. Abdullahi was arraigned on one-count charge bordering on attempted theft. The Chief Magistrate, Mariya Muhammad, gave the ruling after Abdullahi of Mabera… June 1, 2018 In "Metro" Kano - A Kano Magistrates’ court on Monday sentenced a 21-year-old labourer, Bashir Abdullahi, to one month in prison for stealing six chickens. The Magistrate, Fatima Muhammad, sentenced Abdullahi after he pleaded guilty to the offence of theft, contrary to Section 288 of the Penal Code. Muhammad, however, gave the… July 28, 2015 In "News" By Amen Gajira Minna - A Minna Magistrates’ Court on Tuesday sentenced a 20-year-old butcher, Shamsudeen Idris, to three months in prison for stealing an IPad and household items. Magistrate Sa’adatu Gambo sentenced Idris after he pleaded guilty to house breaking, mischief and theft contrary to sections 79, 347, 327… July 30, 2019 In "Metro"